      <byline class="normalized_byline">Strugatch, Warren</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Comtec Telecommunications Corp announces $1.5 million contract in cojunction with Telkom South Africa to update South africa's satellite communications network (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Comtech Telecommunications Corporation in Melville (Nasdaq: CMTL) announced a $1.5 million contract to update South Africa's satellite communications network.</p>
        <p>The company will work with Telkom South Africa on an exclusive two-year contract to supply high performance C-band and Ku-band frequency converters.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Comtech Telecommunications Corporation in Melville (Nasdaq: CMTL) announced a $1.5 million contract to update South Africa's satellite communications network.</p>
        <p>The company will work with Telkom South Africa on an exclusive two-year contract to supply high performance C-band and Ku-band frequency converters.</p>
        <p>The contract calls for immediate delivery of more than $400,000 worth of goods.</p>
        <p>IN BRIEF E-mail address: libiz@nytimes.com</p>
